<br>
Then suddenly Cyanna barged into the Queen's hut, without the permission of the guards or Hippolyte.  Hipp's eyes narrowed quickly.  Her feelings so confused for the moment and then by the intrusion.  <br>
<br>
The two guards quickly ran inside and grabbed Cyanna by both arms.  One bowing to Hipp, &quot;I am sorry, my Vasilissa.  She just barged right in without any permission.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Hippolyte began to glare at Cyanna, as she spoke to Otere.  &quot;How dare you just enter my hut?!&quot;  Her voice was almost growling. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A> at: 5/12/03 8:34:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otereshamaness>OtereShamaness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#993300>(5/12/03 8:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=474.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.members.aol.com/darkmoonhex/images/otere.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *sigh*...</span><hr size=1> Otere had not expected this reaction.  She had in her mind an image of the great Queen running into her arms.  This was far from that.  Her auburn occulars shot wide open when her daughter spoke and with a hint of fear in them, she shot a glance towards Yakut pleading for help with them.  The Shamaness turned and brought her attention to the one who ruined it all.<br>
<br>
Her heart was shattered and this moment could not be saved.  Because of Cyanna what would have been her happy moment became her worst nightmare.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cyanna, I have given birth before.  I do not need information from you.  From you, of all people.  I have survived two births, one including the great Queen Hippolyte. And you merely one.  I have also delivered many.  So keep your supposed scroll of Gabrielle.&quot;<br>
<br>
An intense anger filled inside her as she closed her eyes to hold back the feeling and the tears stinging to come out.  She looked back to Queen Hippolyte with a longing in her eyes and heart only to embrace her daughter.<br>
<br>
&quot;My Queen, I did not want to upset you.  I wanted to reunite with my family.  But not in this manner...not like this.&quot; <p>_.·.Øtere, §hamaness of the N¤rth.·._<br>
